'''Japhug''' is a [[Rgyalrong languages|Rgyalrong]] language spoken in [[Barkam County]], [[Ngawa Tibetan and Qiang Autonomous Prefecture|Rngaba]], [[Sichuan]], [[China]], in the three [[Townships of the People's Republic of China|townships]] of Gdong-brgyad ({{zh|s=龙尔甲|p=Lóng'rjiǎ}}, Japhug {{IPA-all|ʁdɯrɟɤt}}), Gsar-rdzong ({{zh|s=沙尔宗|p=Shā'rzōng}}, Japhug {{IPA-all|sarndzu}}) and Da-tshang ({{zh|s=大藏|p=Dàzàng}}, Japhug {{IPA-all|tatsʰi}}).

The [[endonym]] of the Japhug language is {{IPA-all|kɯrɯ skɤt}}.  The name Japhug {{IPA-all|tɕɤpʰɯ}} ({{zh|p=Chábǎo|s=茶堡}}) refers in Japhug to the area comprising Gsar-rdzong and Da-tshang, while that of Gdong-brgyad is also known as {{IPA-all|sɤŋu}} (Jacques 2004), but speakers of Situ Rgyalrong use this name to refer to the whole Japhug-speaking area.

== Phonology==

Japhug is the only toneless Rgyalrong language. It has 49 consonants and seven vowels.

