'''Jatoi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|'''جتوئی'''}}}}) is a [[Baloch people|Baloch]] tribe settled in [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]], [[Punjab (region)|Punjab]] and [[Sindh]] provinces of [[Pakistan]].
== Structure == The Jatoi tribe is one of the biggest tribes of [[Baloch people|Baloch]]. They originated in [[Kachhi District|Bolan district]] Balochistan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesindhtimes.com/pak/former-caretaker-prime-minister-ghulam-mustafa-jatoi-passes-away/|title=Former caretaker prime minister Ghulam Mustafa Jatoi passes away |date=21 November 2009|publisher=The Sindh Times}}</ref> The Jatoi tribe is involved in armed clashes with other tribes in Sindh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1044260|title=Three Jatoi men killed in tribal clash|first=The Newspaper's|last=Correspondent|date=21 September 2013|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/511213/tribal-clash-youth-killed-two-women-kidnapped/|title=Tribal clash : Youth killed, two women kidnapped|date=23 February 2013|publisher=The Express Tribune}}</ref>
