'''Alayna Ertl''' was a missing 5-year-old girl from [[Watkins, Minnesota]] who was later found murdered.<ref name="BCAPoster">{{cite web|title=Amber Alert Poster: Alayna Ertl|url=https://dps.mn.gov/Documents/Amber-Alert.Ertl.pdf|publisher=Minnesota Bureau of Criminal Apprehension}}</ref><ref name="DailyMail" />  She went missing on Saturday, August 20, 2016 and was last seen alive around 2am Central Daylight Time, according to the [[Amber Alert]] that was issued for her.<ref name="AmberAlert">{{cite news|title=Amber Alert: 5-year-old girl from Watkins, MN|url=http://www.kare11.com/news/local/amber-alert-5-year-old-girl-from-watkins-mn/303534151|accessdate=21 August 2016|agency=Kare 11|publisher=TEGNA}}</ref> When her parents woke up at 8am Saturday, they noted that their daughter, their pickup truck, and the house guest who had stayed with them overnight were gone.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cass County Attorney's Office {{!}} Press Release|url=http://stmedia.startribune.com/documents/SKMBT_C28016082310590.pdf|accessdate=24 April 2017|publisher=startribune.com|date=23 August 2016}}</ref> After her parents reported her missing, her father's cell phone in the truck [[ping (networking utility)|pinged]] a cell tower in [[Todd County, Minnesota]] giving a clue to where she might be.<ref>{{cite news|title=Body of 5-Year-Old Girl Abducted from Meeker County Recovered, Suspect Arrested|url=http://kstp.com/news/alayna-jeanne-ertl-zachary-todd-anderson-meeker-cass-county-abduction-body-found/4240855/?cat=1|accessdate=21 August 2016|publisher=KSTP}}</ref> Her body was located nine hours later in [[Cass County, Minnesota|Cass county]] near the Wilderness Park <ref name="TribuneInitial">{{cite news|title=5-year-old girl reported missing found dead in Cass County|url=http://www.startribune.com/5-year-old-girl-missing-in-meeker-county/390800681/|accessdate=21 August 2016|publisher=Star Tribune}}</ref> in a swampy area.<ref>{{cite news|title=5-year-old Alayna Ertl died of ‘homicidal violence,’ body found in ‘swampy area’|url=http://bringmethenews.com/2016/08/21/5-year-old-alayna-ertl-died-of-homicidal-violence-body-found-in-swampy-area/|accessdate=23 August 2016|date=22 August 2016}}</ref>

The overnight guest, Zachary Todd Anderson, a softball teammate of the girl's father, is believed to have stolen the family's white 2002 [[GMC (automobile)|GMC]] [[GMC Sierra|Sierra]] pickup truck during the abduction. He was located in a secluded area around 4:20pm Central Time.<ref name="TribuneInitial" /> Police had tracked the vehicle to Anderson's family's cabin, which was unoccupied when they arrived.<ref>{{cite news|title=Minnesota man arrested over kidnap, murder of co-worker's 5-year-old|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/alayna-jeanne-ertl-found-dead-minnesota-dad-s-co-worker-n635696|accessdate=23 August 2016|publisher=NBC News}}</ref>
When police located Anderson, he was standing knee-deep in a swamp behind the cabin with his wrists slashed. He eventually led them to Alayna's body, which was completely submerged under water.
An autopsy found evidence of sexual assault, and determined the cause of death to be strangulation and blunt force trauma to the head.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/local/2017/05/31/judge-suppresses-ertl-murder-suspects-statement/359057001/|title=Judge suppresses Ertl murder suspect's statement|publisher=}}</ref>

On March 2nd, 2018, Zachary Todd Anderson pleaded guilty to a charge of first-degree murder while committing first-degree criminal sexual conduct. He received Minnesota's mandatory sentence of life in prison without the possibility of parole.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sctimes.com/story/news/local/2018/03/02/alayna-ertls-killer-pleads-guilty-gets-life-sentence/390665002/|title=Alayna Ertl's killer pleads guilty, gets life sentence|publisher=}}</ref>

